Create the environment running the following command in command line:
	conda env create -f environment.yml -n NAMEYOULIKE

Activate the environment using:
	conda activate NAMEYOULIKE

Get the data by running the following commands in the main folder:
	make clean
	make all

If you want to access the most recent twitter data instead. Create a .env file in the main directory with the following access information (use your own key and token):
	export API_key = "whatever"
	export API_secret_key = "whatever"
	export Access_token = "whatever"
	export Access_token_secret = "Whatever"

To checkout/run the main analysis, please go to notebook/Analyze.ipynb
